1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:26,840
Now every time

2
00:00:26,940 --> 00:00:30,880
You hit one more bump in the road

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:34,400
Feel the burden

4
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:38,320
Of another heavy load

5
00:00:38,420 --> 00:00:41,760
Hit by the curves

6
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:45,521
Life's unexpected twists and turns

7
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:49,840
You feel your world is upside down

8
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:52,771
And you're tumblin', tumblin, tumblin'

9
00:00:55,660 --> 00:01:00,000
So take a hold from deep within

10
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:03,880
And find your life once again

11
00:01:03,980 --> 00:01:07,120
You better go down easy

12
00:01:07,220 --> 00:01:11,000
You got a lot to learn

13
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:14,520
You better count your blessings

14
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,920
Or you're gonna crash and burn

15
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:26,040
It was another world, Alabama in 1935.

16
00:01:26,140 --> 00:01:28,960
A harder world for sure.

17
00:01:29,060 --> 00:01:30,760
Middle of the Depression.

18
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:33,640
Not a job to be found for 100 miles

19
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:36,520
once the cotton was in.

20
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:39,840
William and Helen Hemsley would
have been better advised

21
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:43,080
to wait before marrying
and starting a family.

22
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:46,240
But as they usually do, love and passion

23
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:49,040
got in front of logic and patience.

24
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:51,360
And in obedience with the scripture,

25
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:53,360
the Hemsleys set about the business

26
00:01:53,460 --> 00:01:55,320
of being fruitful and multiplying

27
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:59,280
and starting a whole new life
in the big city of Decatur.

28
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,800
Sir.

29
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,280
Say, I was wondering

30
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:20,280
if maybe you got any more work

31
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:21,520
a fellow could do around here...

32
00:02:21,620 --> 00:02:23,600
No, we're done till seeding.

33
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,520
Sir, please.

34
00:02:25,620 --> 00:02:26,880
We got a baby coming due
and there ain't no...

35
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,880
Son, I don't have anything.

36
00:02:29,980 --> 00:02:32,162
There's nothing I can do for you.

37
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:50,284
William, honey. Meet your sons.

38
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:02,164
They're perfect, just like you.

39
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:05,880
Mr. William,

40
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:09,050
y'all got two fine looking boys here.

41
00:03:15,660 --> 00:03:17,840
Tent revivals were a common occurrence

42
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:20,080
in the rural South in the Depression.

43
00:03:20,180 --> 00:03:22,880
People needing healing, prayer,

44
00:03:22,980 --> 00:03:25,920
and just some hope in a
poor and frightening time.

45
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:29,320
For William Hemsley,
all of these applied.

46
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:31,720
What should've been the
happiest day of his life

47
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:34,760
was quickly becoming
the most troublesome.

48
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:39,320
...we first begun

49
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:42,280
Reverend Reece Wade was
a traveling evangelist

50
00:03:42,380 --> 00:03:43,960
out of middle Tennessee.

51
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:47,360
And his message this cold October night

52
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:51,000
would reach right into
William's troubled soul.

53
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:55,762
And it is here that our
story truly begins.

54
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:00,080
Blacks and whites, Jews and Gentiles,

55
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:02,960
all equal in the eyes of the Lord.

56
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:06,000
All equal in the eyes of the Lord!

57
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,200
Amen.

58
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:08,400
And let us never forget.

59
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:10,160
Let us never forget the words

60
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:13,000
of our Lord and savior Jesus Christ,

61
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:17,560
who says it is truly more blessed
to give than to receive.

62
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:19,120
Amen.

63
00:04:19,220 --> 00:04:23,211
It is truly more blessed
to give than to receive.

64
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:36,605
That's my precious wife Louise,
sitting right over here.

65
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:47,647
We miscarried again over Thanksgiving.

66
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:52,160
The doctor over in Birmingham

67
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:56,000
told us to stop trying,

68
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:57,920
or it might be her that goes.

69
00:04:58,020 --> 00:05:02,880
And all the gifts He's given us,

70
00:05:02,980 --> 00:05:05,287
that's the one we wanted most.

71
00:05:06,620 --> 00:05:10,247
All of our dreams were of having a baby.

72
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:15,728
Family of our own...

73
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,489
love...

74
00:05:21,940 --> 00:05:24,361
to take care of.

75
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:33,401
Maybe... maybe y'all could
pray for us tonight.

76
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,568
For our own miracle.

77
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:01,720
What?

78
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:02,840
Now, I know this sounds...

79
00:06:02,940 --> 00:06:06,120
Crazy? Absolutely insane?

80
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:08,200
- Just listen to me.
- No, William.

81
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:11,040
Just listen!
We can't do it.

82
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:13,280
We can't even feed ourselves.
Now we got two more?

83
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:15,240
I'm not giving away my babies!

84
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:17,720
I'll work two jobs.
I'll work three!

85
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:20,080
Having a job is my job!
And there ain't none!

86
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:22,567
There ain't no work anywhere.

87
00:06:24,940 --> 00:06:27,200
We're drowning.

88
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:30,051
We got nothing and no way to get along.

89
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,840
They'll take them away from
us if we can't feed them.

90
00:06:35,940 --> 00:06:39,160
What if they get sick or
something happens to me?

91
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:41,840
You're going to raise two
babies mending dresses?

92
00:06:41,940 --> 00:06:44,168
So you just give them both up?

93
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:50,600
One.

94
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,560
Now, we can make it with just one.

95
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:54,520
No, William Hemsley.

96
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:57,371
Nobody is taking my babies from me.

97
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:00,687
Never.

98
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:15,525
They're here.

99
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:20,042
All right.

100
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:34,600
Well, I'm sure you're all wondering

101
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:37,087
why I asked you out
here so urgent and all.

102
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:43,042
I heard you at the revival,
reverend, and...

103
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,000
it made me think.

104
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:51,400
And I was talking it
over here with my wife

105
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:54,400
and we want to ask you something.

106
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,960
Let me see if I can make
this a little easier.

107
00:07:57,060 --> 00:08:00,360
The Bible says we're all
brothers and sisters in Christ.

108
00:08:00,460 --> 00:08:04,520
Our job is to love and
look out for one another.

109
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:07,520
Now Louise and I prayed
and talked over this

110
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:10,080
and we want you to have a
love offering given to us.

111
00:08:10,180 --> 00:08:11,680
Oh no.
Thank you but...

112
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:14,320
- Please take it.
- Take it.

113
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:17,680
No, thank you, but that's not
why we wanted to see you.

114
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:20,600
You see, Helen and I have
been praying ourselves

115
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:25,240
and we think God's give
us both some answers.

116
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:26,920
Now, we can give everything we got

117
00:08:27,020 --> 00:08:29,200
to raise one child and that is it.

118
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:34,040
Maybe someone else,
like a man and woman of God,

119
00:08:34,140 --> 00:08:36,320
could give the other
a life we never could.

120
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:38,488
No, no.

121
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:44,800
You're beautiful and blessed people

122
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:47,080
to even consider such a thing.

123
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:51,640
But you're just tired, honey,
and scared and emotional.

124
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:53,720
Times is hard for everybody.

125
00:08:53,820 --> 00:08:55,920
No, we prayed on it like you say to do.

126
00:08:56,020 --> 00:08:57,560
No, William. We can't.

127
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:01,360
You preached it, reverend.

128
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:04,000
It's better to give than receive.

129
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:08,440
You don't know this ain't
God answering your prayers.

130
00:09:08,540 --> 00:09:13,400
Maybe He's got something special
in mind for one of our boys.

131
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:15,600
You see...

132
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:19,160
it's God we're really giving him to.

133
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:21,320
That's what the Lord wants.

134
00:09:21,420 --> 00:09:24,091
We both know it.

135
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:28,687
And you both know it too.

136
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:37,606
The Lord will choose for you.

137
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:14,680
I'll love him good for both of us.

138
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:16,405
Thank you.

139
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:21,164
And God be with you, sister.

140
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:28,520
Dexter Ryan is not to know
until Helen and I pass.

141
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:30,529
Give me your word on that, pastor?

142
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:34,728
Yeah, you have my word.

143
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,200
I don't know what to say.

144
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,320
There's nothing to say.

145
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:50,204
He's God's now anyway.

146
00:10:52,980 --> 00:10:55,048
Now, go.

147
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:22,160
It was not uncommon in
the 1930s to lose a baby.

148
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:23,640
There was a funeral for the child

149
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:26,320
they gave away the next day.

150
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:28,520
All William and Helen could afford

151
00:11:28,620 --> 00:11:31,040
was a shoe box to bury him in.

152
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:34,608
Of course, only they
knew the box was empty.

153
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:02,520
And somewhere, on the road
to their new life as a family,

154
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:05,720
the Reverend Reece Wade
stole away with his new son

155
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:09,240
and dedicated him to
the creator of life itself,

156
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:11,761
the king of the universe.

157
00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:17,800
Amen.

158
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:21,049
Ryan Reece Wade,
welcome to your new life.

159
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:28,000
Christ the Lord is ris'n today

160
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:33,480
Alleluia!

161
00:12:33,580 --> 00:12:38,440
Raise your joys and triumphs high

162
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:42,680
Alleluia!

163
00:12:42,780 --> 00:12:45,000
You'd almost say little Ryan Wade was

164
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:49,200
like any boy in the 1940s,
except for one thing.

165
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:54,280
When he sang a song,
he could bring the roof down.

166
00:12:54,380 --> 00:13:00,120
Nehemiah, Esther, Psalms...

167
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,440
Job.

168
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:05,611
Job. Yeah, Job, Psalms...

169
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:12,920
- Proverbs?
- Proverbs...

170
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:15,487
How many books of the
Bible are there, Daddy?

171
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:20,560
You tell me. Sixty...

172
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:23,000
- 66.
- 66.

173
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:25,080
How many in the Old Testament?

174
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:27,600
- 39.
- 39.

175
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:30,640
You're on number 20 with Proverbs.

176
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:33,446
Now, come on.

177
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:39,520
And do not be conformed to this world,

178
00:13:39,620 --> 00:13:42,480
but transformed by the
renewing of your mind.

179
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:45,040
That you may prove what
is good and acceptable,

180
00:13:45,140 --> 00:13:46,605
the perfect will of God.

181
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:56,487
Jeremiah 29.

182
00:13:58,620 --> 00:14:01,041
For I know the plans...

183
00:14:03,540 --> 00:14:06,166
I have for you.

184
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:17,840
- Declares the Lord.
- Declares the Lord.

185
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:20,720
But when memorizing
proved to be a challenge,

186
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:22,520
Ryan knew instinctively

187
00:14:22,620 --> 00:14:26,160
what every grade school teacher knows.

188
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:28,960
Turn it into a song.

189
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:31,680
Well

190
00:14:31,780 --> 00:14:41,240
I know the plans I have for you

191
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:44,250
Declares the Lord

192
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:53,200
Plans to prosper and not to harm you

193
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:56,120
And then shall call and pray to me

194
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:58,400
And I will listen to ya

195
00:14:58,500 --> 00:15:02,320
And ye shall seek and ye shall find

196
00:15:02,420 --> 00:15:07,520
When you seek with all of your heart

197
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:18,560
Louise was smitten with the boy's gift.

198
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:21,240
Reece accepted it, but, in his view,

199
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:26,082
Ryan was set aside to follow in
his footsteps as a man of God.

200
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:31,720
...price to pay

201
00:15:31,820 --> 00:15:34,800
She walks right in, she walks right out

202
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:38,200
She sing and dance, she jump and shout

203
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:44,600
Whoa, baby,
don't you just walk by me...

204
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:47,644
Am I the master of the fake ID or what?

205
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:56,247
Oh, no thank you.

206
00:15:58,660 --> 00:16:02,320
Come on, man.
You can't be a PK forever.

207
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:03,760
PK?

208
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:06,560
PK. Preacher's Kid.
That's you.

209
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:09,480
"Please Lord,
never let me have any fun."

210
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:12,920
That's what I am, Dino. Besides...

211
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:14,160
I don't like beer.

212
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:16,601
More for me.

213
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:19,251
I like beer a lot.

214
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:26,320
Man! Are you listening to this?

215
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:27,840
Yeah.

216
00:16:27,940 --> 00:16:30,120
Wow.

217
00:16:30,220 --> 00:16:32,527
I ain't never heard
anything like it before.

218
00:16:34,180 --> 00:16:36,320
How come we can't do music
like this back home?

219
00:16:36,420 --> 00:16:39,920
In Tennessee, in your daddy's church?

220
00:16:40,020 --> 00:16:41,440
Cat, you crazy.

221
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:43,840
I ain't talking about church, Dino.

222
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:46,930
I'm just talking about music.

223
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:52,960
She walk right in, she walk right out

224
00:16:53,060 --> 00:16:55,840
A PK is always the wildest at heart.

225
00:16:55,940 --> 00:16:57,760
Baby baby

226
00:16:57,860 --> 00:17:00,486
Don't you just walk by me

227
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:24,720
it's 1:45 in the morning.

228
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:27,400
You been drinking, son?

229
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,960
No, sir.

230
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:31,400
Don't lie to me.

231
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,204
I ain't lying, Daddy.

232
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,840
You smell like smoke.

233
00:17:37,940 --> 00:17:39,120
I wasn't smoking either.

234
00:17:39,220 --> 00:17:40,320
Where you been?

235
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:42,640
At Dino's place.

236
00:17:42,740 --> 00:17:44,171
Is that so?

237
00:17:45,780 --> 00:17:48,720
I drove by Dino's when I
was out looking for you.

238
00:17:48,820 --> 00:17:51,924
Must've just missed you.

239
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:56,760
I was at a roadhouse across County Line.

240
00:17:56,860 --> 00:17:57,520
What?

241
00:17:57,620 --> 00:17:58,800
Daddy, it ain't what you think.

242
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:00,600
A honky-tonk?

243
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:02,000
Well, I knew if I told you,
you'd never let me go.

244
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:03,440
You're underage!

245
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:05,560
And you're going into the ministry.

246
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,640
I went to listen to some music, Daddy.

247
00:18:07,740 --> 00:18:09,360
What did I do that's so wrong?

248
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:11,722
You didn't tell me the truth,
that's what.

249
00:18:14,380 --> 00:18:16,840
Dance, dance, dance, everybody now

250
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:19,440
Dance, dance, dance

251
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:21,080
Everybody's doing it

252
00:18:21,180 --> 00:18:23,960
It's boogie-woogie rock and roll

253
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:26,367
Yeah

254
00:18:28,420 --> 00:18:29,960
Yeah, that's a good song, cuz.

255
00:18:30,060 --> 00:18:32,320
Yeah, man.
We need more guys though.

256
00:18:32,420 --> 00:18:33,920
Well, we need more everything.

257
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:35,480
Man, we get some guys in here.

258
00:18:35,580 --> 00:18:37,560
I'll sing the songs, write the songs.

259
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:39,880
You play the drums.
It's all I want to do.

260
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:41,640
Hey, you call the tune, I'll play it.

261
00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:44,411
- Let's do it.
- Yeah, let's do it, oh!

262
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,720
Forty years.

263
00:18:48,820 --> 00:18:53,440
Forty years wandering the desert.

264
00:18:53,540 --> 00:18:56,120
Looking for a sign.

265
00:18:56,220 --> 00:19:00,000
Praying for an answer,

266
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:02,320
a direction.

267
00:19:02,420 --> 00:19:04,568
But sometimes...

268
00:19:05,660 --> 00:19:08,206
