Heh. Jenny, last month

1161
01:18:06,740 --> 01:18:10,000
I preached the best sermon
of my whole career.

1162
01:18:10,100 --> 01:18:12,040
Oh, it was outstanding.

1163
01:18:12,140 --> 01:18:14,600
And Ed Nichols reminds me,

1164
01:18:14,700 --> 01:18:17,720
I preached the same one a year ago.

1165
01:18:17,820 --> 01:18:20,480
And I said, "Brother Nichols,
what's wrong with that?

1166
01:18:20,580 --> 01:18:22,000
You just got blessed twice."

1167
01:18:22,100 --> 01:18:27,047
Oh yeah. It's time.

1168
01:18:28,380 --> 01:18:29,880
You ready for him to
be home all the time?

1169
01:18:29,980 --> 01:18:33,000
Oh, I been waiting many a year.

1170
01:18:33,100 --> 01:18:35,480
But I finished the race.

1171
01:18:35,580 --> 01:18:39,520
Wasn't always pretty,
sometimes it wasn't much fun.

1172
01:18:39,620 --> 01:18:41,440
But I got there.

1173
01:18:41,540 --> 01:18:44,800
There isn't a better feeling
this side of heaven.

1174
01:18:44,900 --> 01:18:48,527
Congratulations, Daddy.
Really.

1175
01:18:50,300 --> 01:18:54,400
I want you to have that
same feeling, son.

1176
01:18:54,500 --> 01:18:56,120
It's not too late.

1177
01:18:56,220 --> 01:18:58,440
Oh, Daddy!
This isn't the time.

1178
01:18:58,540 --> 01:19:01,680
Let's just have a calm
family supper without any...

1179
01:19:01,780 --> 01:19:04,200
No, now is the time!

1180
01:19:04,300 --> 01:19:08,000
He may be all grown up,
but we're his parents.

1181
01:19:08,100 --> 01:19:12,720
What are you going to do, Ryan?

1182
01:19:12,820 --> 01:19:15,000
You going to sit inside the house

1183
01:19:15,100 --> 01:19:16,840
and mourn for the rest of your life?

1184
01:19:16,940 --> 01:19:18,480
You know what, y'all?

1185
01:19:18,580 --> 01:19:21,960
You will honor your father by listening.

1186
01:19:22,060 --> 01:19:24,240
Whether you want to hear this or not.

1187
01:19:24,340 --> 01:19:27,320
I have heard it, Daddy.
A hundred times.

1188
01:19:27,420 --> 01:19:29,120
Why?

1189
01:19:29,220 --> 01:19:32,160
Why do you keep running from this, son?

1190
01:19:32,260 --> 01:19:35,200
God set you apart, son.

1191
01:19:35,300 --> 01:19:37,482
No, He didn't!

1192
01:19:39,380 --> 01:19:41,840
Oh, I know the story, Daddy.

1193
01:19:41,940 --> 01:19:44,800
I know it real well.

1194
01:19:44,900 --> 01:19:47,720
You dedicated me to God.

1195
01:19:47,820 --> 01:19:49,880
I know you have a vision for my life.

1196
01:19:49,980 --> 01:19:54,600
Well, you know what?
It's not my vision, Daddy.

1197
01:19:54,700 --> 01:19:57,120
The call you heard was for
your life, not mine, not for me.

1198
01:19:57,220 --> 01:20:00,720
I'm trying to help you, son.

1199
01:20:00,820 --> 01:20:02,280
Please, will you, contain yourself!

1200
01:20:02,380 --> 01:20:04,720
I'm trying to help the boy.

1201
01:20:04,820 --> 01:20:06,440
Daddy, what's wrong?

1202
01:20:06,540 --> 01:20:09,080
Daddy? What is it, honey?

1203
01:20:09,180 --> 01:20:10,480
Oh dear!

1204
01:20:10,580 --> 01:20:12,400
Oh, Jenny!

1205
01:20:12,500 --> 01:20:14,040
- Okay, I'm coming.
- Daddy, what's wrong?

1206
01:20:14,140 --> 01:20:15,600
I think he's having a heart attack.

1207
01:20:15,700 --> 01:20:17,160
Mom, you call an ambulance.
Call an ambulance, Mom.

1208
01:20:17,260 --> 01:20:18,520
My pills!

1209
01:20:18,620 --> 01:20:19,920
I'll get them, Daddy, I'll get them.

1210
01:20:20,020 --> 01:20:21,240
- It's all right.
- Get my pills.

1211
01:20:21,340 --> 01:20:22,680
It's all right.

1212
01:20:33,820 --> 01:20:35,440
We're gettin' you help, honey.

1213
01:20:35,540 --> 01:20:37,040
We'll ride with y'all.

1214
01:20:37,140 --> 01:20:38,680
We're right here, honey.
We're right here.

1215
01:20:38,780 --> 01:20:40,200
I'll follow, Mama.
I'm right behind you.

1216
01:20:40,300 --> 01:20:42,560
In the name of God
Almighty and Jesus Christ,

1217
01:20:42,660 --> 01:20:44,046
I command the Holy Spirit...

1218
01:20:45,660 --> 01:20:49,890
I'm sorry, Daddy. I'm sorry.

1219
01:21:55,660 --> 01:21:57,560
Our dear son.

1220
01:21:57,660 --> 01:21:59,840
If you are reading these words

1221
01:21:59,940 --> 01:22:03,567
it means your mother and I
have passed from this life.

1222
01:22:07,780 --> 01:22:10,680
Time has come for you
to know who you are

1223
01:22:10,780 --> 01:22:13,326
and where you come from.

1224
01:22:16,220 --> 01:22:18,920
You were born to a mama
and daddy who love you

1225
01:22:19,020 --> 01:22:22,488
but can't give you the life we want.

1226
01:22:24,500 --> 01:22:27,880
We believe God has put you
here for something special

1227
01:22:27,980 --> 01:22:32,210
and we asked a man of God
to raise you up proper like.

1228
01:22:34,940 --> 01:22:37,360
You have an identical twin brother

1229
01:22:37,460 --> 01:22:40,450
who is reading a letter
just like yours right now.

1230
01:22:44,940 --> 01:22:48,440
So forgive us and understand

1231
01:22:48,540 --> 01:22:50,960
this is what we had to do.

1232
01:22:51,060 --> 01:22:54,050
We love you and will see you in heaven.

1233
01:22:55,780 --> 01:22:57,680
Your daddy, your momma,

1234
01:22:57,780 --> 01:23:01,407
William and Helen Hemsley.

1235
01:23:21,740 --> 01:23:22,720
Hello?

1236
01:23:22,820 --> 01:23:24,600
It was a mild heart attack.

1237
01:23:24,700 --> 01:23:26,200
He's going to be okay.

1238
01:23:26,300 --> 01:23:27,960
Think of coming down?

1239
01:23:28,060 --> 01:23:31,040
No. Not right now.

1240
01:23:31,140 --> 01:23:33,971
Ryan, your father wants to see you.

1241
01:23:35,460 --> 01:23:37,080
Honey?

1242
01:23:38,980 --> 01:23:41,000
Tell him I'm glad he's all right.

1243
01:23:41,100 --> 01:23:42,640
Tell Mama...

1244
01:23:42,740 --> 01:23:46,880
tell her I know now, and I understand.

1245
01:23:46,980 --> 01:23:48,640
Understand what?

1246
01:23:48,740 --> 01:23:50,444
She'll know.

1247
01:24:58,540 --> 01:25:00,529
Now, what can I get for you?

1248
01:25:01,700 --> 01:25:04,480
I...

1249
01:25:04,580 --> 01:25:06,603
How about a whiskey?

1250
01:25:09,540 --> 01:25:12,450
That will cure your ills, my friend.

1251
01:25:17,100 --> 01:25:20,360
Ryan? Ryan Wade?

1252
01:25:20,460 --> 01:25:23,131
Down here.

1253
01:25:24,740 --> 01:25:26,320
I can't believe this.

1254
01:25:26,420 --> 01:25:29,360
Darling, darling,
do you know who this is?

1255
01:25:29,460 --> 01:25:31,120
No, baby.

1256
01:25:31,220 --> 01:25:32,640
I told you I knew people.

1257
01:25:32,740 --> 01:25:34,160
Maybe now you'll be nicer to me.

1258
01:25:34,260 --> 01:25:37,280
This is none other than The identical.

1259
01:25:37,380 --> 01:25:39,440
What are you doing here?

1260
01:25:39,540 --> 01:25:41,640
You wouldn't believe me if I told you.

1261
01:25:41,740 --> 01:25:42,880
Name's Damon.

1262
01:25:43,980 --> 01:25:47,200
I saw you once in Atlanta.

1263
01:25:47,300 --> 01:25:49,760
Man, I about died. I thought
you was The Dream himself.

1264
01:25:49,860 --> 01:25:52,640
How did you get so dang good anyway?

1265
01:25:52,740 --> 01:25:55,640
Born to it I guess.

1266
01:25:55,740 --> 01:25:58,720
Miss, if you don't mind

1267
01:25:58,820 --> 01:26:00,880
I'm going to trade this
in for something else.

1268
01:26:00,980 --> 01:26:03,160
- A Dr. Pepper or something.
- Oh, yeah.

1269
01:26:03,260 --> 01:26:05,249
Put it on my tab, darling.

1270
01:26:10,180 --> 01:26:12,440
Gave it up, huh?

1271
01:26:12,540 --> 01:26:14,920
Man, that's a shame.

1272
01:26:15,020 --> 01:26:18,240
How did you get into this?

1273
01:26:18,340 --> 01:26:20,800
I was pouring drinks at his hotel once.

1274
01:26:20,900 --> 01:26:22,920
He stopped and talked to me.

1275
01:26:23,020 --> 01:26:25,560
Treated me like a real human being.

1276
01:26:25,660 --> 01:26:27,240
Like he cared what I had to say.

1277
01:26:27,340 --> 01:26:30,284
First average size person ever did that.

1278
01:26:31,940 --> 01:26:33,849
Changed my life.

1279
01:26:37,300 --> 01:26:39,720
I see you've still got your chai though,

1280
01:26:39,820 --> 01:26:41,120
just like his.

1281
01:26:41,220 --> 01:26:44,080
Yeah, why did he wear one?

1282
01:26:44,180 --> 01:26:45,960
- He was Jewish.
- What?

1283
01:26:46,060 --> 01:26:48,360
On his mother's side.
Look it up.

1284
01:26:48,460 --> 01:26:49,720
Really?

1285
01:26:49,820 --> 01:26:53,560
A Christian and a Jew.
Same guy. Heh.

1286
01:26:53,660 --> 01:26:56,320
He used to say he was
covering his bases.

1287
01:26:56,420 --> 01:26:58,760
You believe that?
Isn't that great?

1288
01:26:58,860 --> 01:27:00,246
Yeah.

1289
01:27:04,460 --> 01:27:06,688
You're looking for
something, aren't you?

1290
01:27:08,380 --> 01:27:09,840
Maybe.

1291
01:27:09,940 --> 01:27:14,280
Let me give you a
little hint, Ryan Wade.

1292
01:27:14,380 --> 01:27:19,080
It ain't here, but keep looking.

1293
01:27:19,180 --> 01:27:23,080
You'll find it eventually.
Well, I'm up next.

1294
01:27:23,180 --> 01:27:27,205
Stick around. You might
learn something, identical.

1295
01:27:29,900 --> 01:27:32,002
